body.pre:
  CAP_SETGID
	Pozwala nas setgid(2) manipulation;
	Pozwala nas setgroups(2);
	Pozwala nas forged gids on socket credentials passing.

  CAP_SETUID
	Pozwala nas set*uid(2) manipulation (including fsuid);
	Pozwala nas forged pids on socket credentials passing.

  CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE
	Pozwala nas binding to TCP/UDP sockets below 1024;
	Pozwala nas binding to ATM VCIs below 32.

  CAP_NET_ADMIN
	Pozwala na interface configuration;
	Pozwala na administration of IP firewall, masquerading and accounting;
	Pozwala na setting debug option on sockets;
	Pozwala na modification of routing tables;
	Pozwala na setting arbitrary process / process group ownership on sockets;
	Pozwala na binding to any address for transparent proxying;
	Pozwala na setting TOS (type of service);
	Pozwala na setting promiscuous mode;
	Pozwala na clearing driver statistics;
	Pozwala na multicasting;
	Pozwala na read/write of devicespecific registers;
	Pozwala na activation of ATM control sockets.

  CAP_NET_RAW
	Pozwala na use of RAW sockets;
	Pozwala na use of PACKET sockets.

  CAP_IPC_LOCK
	Pozwala na tworzenie blokady na segmentach pamięci współdzielonej;
	Pozwala na wykonanie mlock/mlockall (co nie ma nic wspólnego z IPC).

  CAP_SYS_MODULE
	Insert and remove kernel modules  modify kernel without limit;
	Modify cap_bset.

  CAP_SYS_RAWIO
	Pozwala na ioperm/iopl access;
	Pozwala na sending USB messages to any device via /proc/bus/usb.

  CAP_SYS_ADMIN
	Pozwala na configuration of the secure attention key;
	Pozwala na administration of the random device;
	Pozwala na examination and configuration of disk quotas;
	Pozwala na configuring the kernel's syslog (printk behaviour);
	Pozwala na ustawianie nazwy domeny;
	Pozwala na ustawianie nazwy hosta;
	Pozwala na wywoływanie bdflush();
	Pozwala na mount() and umount(), setting up new smb connection;
	Pozwala na some autofs root ioctls;
	Pozwala na nfsservctl; Pozwala na VM86_REQUEST_IRQ;
	Pozwala na to read/write pci config on alpha; Pozwala na irix_prctl on mips (setstacksize);
	Pozwala na flushing all cache on m68k (sys_cacheflush);
	Pozwala na removing semaphores; Used instead of CAP_CHOWN to "chown" IPC message queues, semaphores and shared memory;
	Pozwala na locking/unlocking of shared memory segment;
	Pozwala na włączanie/wyłączanie swapu;
	Pozwala na forged pids on socket credentials passing;
	Pozwala na setting readahead and flushing buffers on block devices;
	Pozwala na setting geometry in floppy driver;
	Pozwala na turning DMA on/off in xd driver;
	Pozwala na administration of md devices (mostly the above, but some extra ioctls);
	Pozwala na tuning the ide driver;
	Pozwala na access to the nvram device;
	Pozwala na administration of apm_bios, serial and bttv (TV) device;
	Pozwala na manufacturer commands in isdn CAPI support driver;
	Pozwala na reading nonstandardized portions of pci configuration space;
	Pozwala na DDI debug ioctl on sbpcd driver;
	Pozwala na setting up serial ports;
	Pozwala na sending raw qic117 commands;
	Pozwala na enabling/disabling tagged queuing on SCSI controllers and sending arbitrary SCSI commands;
	Pozwala na setting encryption key on loopback filesystem.

  CAP_SYS_RESOURCE 
	Override resource limits. Set resource limits;
	Override quota limits;
	Override reserved space on ext2 filesystem;
	Modify data journaling mode on ext3 filesystem 
	(uses journaling resources); NOTE: ext2 honors fsuid when checking for
	resource overrides, so you can override using fsuid too;
	Override size restrictions on IPC message queues;
	Pozwala na more than 64hz interrupts from the realtime clock;
	Override max number of consoles on console allocation;
	Override max number of keymaps.

  CAP_SYS_TIME
	Pozwala na manipulacje zegarem systemowym;
	Pozwala na wywołąnie irix_stime na architekturze mips;
	Pozwala na ustawienie zegara czasu rzeczywistego.
